The governments of Costa Rica, the Netherlands, the Republic of Korea, the Republic of Zambia, and the United States have announced that they will co-host the second Summit for Democracy on March 29-30, 2023. This summit aims to showcase how democracies can address the world's challenges and deliver for their citizens. It will be held in a virtual, plenary format, followed by hybrid gatherings in each participating country. The summit will highlight the progress made by Summit partners on their commitments during the Year of Action and emphasize the importance of transparent and accountable governance in achieving lasting prosperity, peace, and justice. The leaders participating in the summit are looking forward to demonstrating the value of democratic renewal and taking concrete action to address the unprecedented challenges of our time.